SIMPLE: insincere
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insincere
<hw>In`sin*cere"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>insincerus</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Sincere</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not being in truth what one appears to be; not
sincere; dissembling; hypocritical; disingenuous; deceitful; false; --
said of persons; also of speech, thought; etc.; <as>as,
<ex>insincere</ex> declarations</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disappointing; imperfect; unsound.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To render sleep's soft blessings <qex>insincere</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Dissembling; hollow; hypocritical; deceptive
deceitful; false; disingenuous; untrustworthy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insincerely</ent>⟦br⟧
